[SN]TITLE[SN]
Merseyside officer 'contacted victims for sexual purposes'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A police officer has been charged over allegations he made "persistent contact" with victims of crime for "his own sexual purposes".

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Det Con Michael McMillan, 32, from Merseyside Police has been charged with misconduct in public office.
The allegations relate to his position as a detective constable with the Family Crime Investigation Unit.
He is due to appear before Liverpool Magistrates' Court on 3 December. He is currently suspended from duty.
The allegations have been the subject of an investigation by Merseyside Police's anti-corruption unit and were managed by the Independent Police Complaints Commission.
